So not a big deal, but what do you think about instead of just returning a `Future.successful()` here if there are no arguments, to instead do the `interactiveReset()`. Main reason being right now for clients that won't ever send in params, they have to register the command separately because it _has_ to be registerd with the arguments field of an empty array. So for `coc-metals` for example, that means I can't just add a one-liner here:
https://github.com/scalameta/coc-metals/blob/630450a7cd1e777ddf1392e672838de2e2965b7c/src/index.ts#L248-L260

and instead I'd need to do this:

```javascript
    registerCommand("metals.reset-choice-interactive", () => {
      client.sendRequest(ExecuteCommandRequest.type, {
        command: "reset-choice",
        arguments: [],
      });
    });
```
Again, it's a nitpick, but for me having to set arguments to an empty array all the time doesn't make sense. So it might be nice that if the server gets the `reset-choice` request with no params, it still works. What do you think?

